        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 3:31PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 330 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Glouster, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glouster, Corning, Trimble, Rendville, and Burr Oak State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
